# Living Design Doc Skeleton — {{DOMAIN}}

The `{{DOMAIN_LOWER}}-feature-design` orchestrator writes one of these per feature to
`{{WIKI_ROOT}}/{{DOMAIN}}/designs/YYYY-MM-DD-<feature>-design.md`. It is a living document:
status moves `proposed → accepted`, and on acceptance its decisions are distilled into atomic
pages via the wiki bridge `persist()` procedure.

```markdown
---
type: wiki-design
wiki: {{DOMAIN}}
feature: <kebab-feature-name>
status: proposed        # proposed | accepted | superseded
Created: YYYY-MM-DD
Updated: YYYY-MM-DD
grounding:              # pages/sources the Context Brief cited
  - [[page-name]]
supersedes: null        # path to a prior design this replaces, if any
tags: [{{TAG_PREFIX}}design]
---

# <Feature> — Design

## Problem
<the user-facing problem, one paragraph. What pain, for whom.>

## Context Brief
<verbatim output of the wiki-bridge ground() calls. The differentiator: what the wiki
already knows before we propose anything.>

### Decided-against / constraints
<what was previously rejected, and the invariants this feature must not break. If the wiki
already settled this, say so here and stop.>

## Scope
**In scope:** <locked, after the product lens>
**NOT in scope:** <explicitly cut>
**Already exists:** <what we reuse instead of building>

## Alternatives considered
<2–3 forced alternatives with effort / risk / reuse, each citing wiki prior art.>

## Architecture
<components, responsibilities, and an ASCII diagram of the data/control flow.>

## Data flow & edge cases
<happy path + shadow paths: nil input, empty input, upstream error. Name each.>

## Test plan
<what proves it works: unit, integration, the failure modes that must be covered. ASCII
coverage diagram if non-trivial.>

## Performance
<critical-path budget, expected load, what to measure.>

## Implementation tasks
- [ ] P1 — <must-ship>
- [ ] P2 — <should>
- [ ] P3 — <nice-to-have>

## Open questions
<unresolved, with who/what would resolve them.>

## Decision log
- YYYY-MM-DD — <decision> (rationale; cites [[page]])
```
